<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Not sure if this is a bug or feature, but the Zend_Db adapters' {{describeTable()}} method seems to allow for silent failure. For example, with the pdo_pgsql adapter, if the schema is incorrect, the method will return an empty array.</p>

<p>I would expect an exception to be thrown if {{describeTable()}} cannot successfully complete its assigned duty.</p>

<p>If instead the expected behavior for failure is to return an empty array, then this should be documented.</p>

